dct_title_s: Inside passage between Bath and Boothbay Harbor
dct_description_sm: from a trigonometrical survey under the direction of A.D. Bache and B. Peirce, Superintendents of the Survey of the Coast of the United States ; triangulation by A.W. Evans ... ; topography by R.M. Bache ... [et at.] ; hydrography by Lieuts. Comdg. S.D. Trenchard ... [et al.].
Depths shown by shading and soundings.
"Re-issued May 1884 J.E. Hilgard Superintendent, verified C.O. Boutelle, Assistant in charge of Office ; date of first publication, 1867."
North oriented to upper left corner.
Includes charts on lights and tides.
